President Joe Biden delivered a speech at Ebenezer Baptist Church in Atlanta, Georgia, commemorating what would have been Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.'s 94th birthday. He emphasized the importance of Dr. King's moral vision and the need to continue working towards justice and equality. President Biden discussed the ongoing battle for the soul of America and the choices that need to be made to uphold democracy, community, and love over hate. He urged the nation to remember Dr. King's message and to continue walking the path towards a more perfect union. The President also spoke about the significance of the statues of Dr. King and Rosa Parks in his Oval Office and the inspiration they provide. He concluded by expressing hope and faith in the American people's capacity to create a better future.